NEW YORK, United States of America, June 10, 2019/APO Group/ --
                                                        
                            The Secretary-General is outraged by reports that at least 95 civilians, including women and children, have been killed and many injured following an attack yesterday on Sobanou-Kou village, Mopti region, in central Mali.


                                He strongly condemns this attack and calls on the Malian authorities to investigate this tragedy and to bring the perpetrators to justice
                            

He strongly condemns this attack and calls on the Malian authorities to investigate this tragedy and to bring the perpetrators to justice.Â  The Secretary-General expresses his heartfelt condolences to the families of the victims, the people and the Government of Mali, and wishes a speedy recovery to the injured.



The Secretary-General appeals to all Malian stakeholders to show restraint and to refrain from retaliatory acts. He urges the Government and all actors to engage in intercommunal dialogue to resolve tensions and differences.